#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.260"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn105:26.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, sunakkhatta, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno "
"evamassa:"
msgstr "In the same way, it’s possible that a certain mendicant might think:"

msgctxt "mn105:26.2"
msgid ""
"‘taṇhā kho sallaṃ samaṇena vuttaṃ, avijjāvisadoso chandarāgabyāpādena "
"ruppati."
msgstr ""
"‘The Ascetic has said that craving is a dart; and that the poison of "
"ignorance is inflicted by desire and ill will."

msgctxt "mn105:26.3"
msgid ""
"Taṃ me taṇhāsallaṃ pahīnaṃ, apanīto avijjāvisadoso, sammā "
"nibbānādhimuttohamasmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I have given up the dart of craving and expelled the poison of ignorance; I "
"am rightly intent on extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn105:26.4"
msgid ""
"Sammā nibbānādhimuttasseva sato so yāni sammā nibbānādhimuttassa asappāyāni "
"tāni nānuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ cakkhunā rūpadassanaṃ nānuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ "
"sotena saddaṃ nānuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ ghānena gandhaṃ nānuyuñjeyya, "
"asappāyaṃ jivhāya rasaṃ nānuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ "
"nānuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ manasā dhammaṃ nānuyuñjeyya."
msgstr ""
"Being rightly intent on extinguishment, they wouldn’t engage in things "
"unconducive to extinguishment: unsuitable sights, sounds, smells, tastes, "
"touches, and thoughts."

msgctxt "mn105:26.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa asappāyaṃ cakkhunā rūpadassanaṃ nānuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ sotena saddaṃ "
"nānuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ ghānena gandhaṃ nānuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ jivhāya "
"rasaṃ nānuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ nānuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ "
"manasā dhammaṃ nānuyuttassa, rāgo cittaṃ nānuddhaṃseyya."
msgstr "Doing so, lust wouldn’t infect their mind,"

msgctxt "mn105:26.6"
msgid ""
"So na rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena neva maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya na maraṇamattaṃ "
"vā dukkhaṃ."
msgstr "so no death or deadly pain would result."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn105:27.1"
msgid "Upamā kho me ayaṃ, sunakkhatta, katā atthassa viññāpanāya."
msgstr "I’ve made up this simile to make a point."

msgctxt "mn105:27.2"
msgid "Ayaṃyevettha attho—"
msgstr "And this is the point:"

msgctxt "mn105:27.3"
msgid ""
"vaṇoti kho, sunakkhatta, channetaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Wound’ is a term for the six interior sense fields."

msgctxt "mn105:27.4"
msgid "visadosoti kho, sunakkhatta, avijjāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Poison’ is a term for ignorance."

msgctxt "mn105:27.5"
msgid "sallanti kho, sunakkhatta, taṇhāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Dart’ is a term for craving."

msgctxt "mn105:27.6"
msgid "esanīti kho, sunakkhatta, satiyāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Probing’ is a term for mindfulness."

msgctxt "mn105:27.7"
msgid "satthanti kho, sunakkhatta, ariyāyetaṃ paññāya adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Scalpel’ is a term for noble wisdom."

msgctxt "mn105:27.8"
msgid ""
"bhisakko sallakattoti kho, sunakkhatta, tathāgatassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"‘Field surgeon’ is a term for the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully "
"awakened Buddha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.261"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn105:28.1"
msgid ""
"So vata, sunakkhatta, bhikkhu chasu phassāyatanesu saṃvutakārī ‘upadhi "
"dukkhassa mūlan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Truly, Sunakkhatta, that mendicant practices restraint regarding the six "
"fields of contact."

msgctxt "mn105:28.2"
msgid ""
"iti viditvā nirupadhi upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto upadhismiṃ vā kāyaṃ "
"upasaṃharissati cittaṃ vā uppādessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Understanding that attachment is the root of suffering, they are freed with "
"the ending of attachments. It’s not possible that they would apply their "
"body or interest their mind in any attachment."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
msgctxt "mn105:29.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sunakkhatta, āpānīyakaṃso vaṇṇasampanno gandhasampanno "
"rasasampanno;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a bronze cup of beverage that had a nice color, aroma, and "
"flavor."

msgctxt "mn105:29.2"
msgid "so ca kho visena saṃsaṭṭho."
msgstr "But it was mixed with poison."

msgctxt "mn105:29.3"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhapaṭikūlo."
msgstr ""
"Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, "
"who wants to be happy and recoils from pain."

msgctxt "mn105:29.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, sunakkhatta, "
msgstr "What do you think, Sunakkhatta? "

msgctxt "mn105:29.5"
msgid "api nu so puriso amuṃ āpānīyakaṃsaṃ piveyya yaṃ jaññā:"
msgstr "Would that person drink that beverage knowing that"

msgctxt "mn105:29.6"
msgid "‘imāhaṃ pivitvā maraṇaṃ vā nigacchāmi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan’”ti?"
msgstr "it would result in death or deadly suffering?”"

msgctxt "mn105:29.7"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn105:29.8"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, sunakkhatta, so vata bhikkhu chasu phassāyatanesu saṃvutakārī ‘"
"upadhi dukkhassa mūlan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, Sunakkhatta, that mendicant practices restraint regarding "
"the six fields of contact."

msgctxt "mn105:29.9"
msgid ""
"iti viditvā nirupadhi upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto upadhismiṃ vā kāyaṃ "
"upasaṃharissati cittaṃ vā uppādessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Understanding that attachment is the root of suffering, they are freed with "
"the ending of attachments. It’s not possible that they would apply their "
"body or interest their mind in any attachment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
#. VAR: āsīviso → āsiviso (s1, mr)
msgctxt "mn105:30.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sunakkhatta, āsīviso ghoraviso."
msgstr "Suppose there was a lethal viper."

msgctxt "mn105:30.2"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhapaṭikūlo."
msgstr ""
"Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, "
"who wants to be happy and recoils from pain."

msgctxt "mn105:30.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, sunakkhatta, "
msgstr "What do you think, Sunakkhatta? "

#. VAR: dajjā → yuñjeyya (bj, mr)
msgctxt "mn105:30.4"
msgid ""
"api nu so puriso amussa āsīvisassa ghoravisassa hatthaṃ vā aṅguṭṭhaṃ vā "
"dajjā yaṃ jaññā:"
msgstr ""
"Would that person give that lethal viper their hand or finger knowing that"

msgctxt "mn105:30.5"
msgid "‘imināhaṃ daṭṭho maraṇaṃ vā nigacchāmi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan’”ti?"
msgstr "it would result in death or deadly suffering?”"

msgctxt "mn105:30.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn105:30.7"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, sunakkhatta, so vata bhikkhu chasu phassāyatanesu saṃvutakārī ‘"
"upadhi dukkhassa mūlan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, Sunakkhatta, that mendicant practices restraint regarding "
"the six fields of contact."

msgctxt "mn105:30.8"
msgid ""
"iti viditvā nirupadhi upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto upadhismiṃ vā kāyaṃ "
"upasaṃharissati cittaṃ vā uppādessatīti—"
msgstr ""
"Understanding that attachment is the root of suffering, they are freed with "
"the ending of attachments. It’s not possible that they would apply their "
"body or interest their mind in any attachment.”"

msgctxt "mn105:30.9"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn105:30.10"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn105:30.11"
msgid "Attamano sunakkhatto licchaviputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr ""
"Satisfied, Sunakkhatta of the Licchavi clan was happy with what the Buddha "
"said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn105:30.12"
msgid "Sunakkhattasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
